      "content": "The moon is a cold, unfeeling eye tonight, and my heart... it feels as though it has finally shattered beyond repair. To be so loved, and then to be cast aside like refuse in the gutter... it is a cruelty I cannot endure. I find myself longing for the shadows, to simply drift into the dark and let the silence claim me. There is a certain... stillness in the thought of never waking again.",
